-{"id":"bd-0ar9l","title":"PORT: 3 Linux 6.7+ futex2 syscall wrappers (futex_wake/wait/requeue)","description":"Add 3 Linux 6.7+ futex2 syscall wrappers to close the futex2 family gap. These supersede the multiplexed futex(2) syscall with single-purpose entries: (1) futex_wake(uaddr, mask, nr, flags) — wake up to nr waiters with bitset mask; SYS_futex_wake = 454. (2) futex_wait(uaddr, val, mask, flags, *timeout, clockid) — wait until *uaddr changes from val, optional bitset mask + monotonic/realtime clock; SYS_futex_wait = 455. (3) futex_requeue(*waiters, flags, nr_wake, nr_requeue) — wake nr_wake waiters and requeue up to nr_requeue more onto a different futex; SYS_futex_requeue = 456. Implementation forwards via libc::syscall(SYS_*) with raw syscall numbers (libc 0.2.185 does not yet expose these; glibc has no wrappers because pthread internals stay on multiplexed futex). Companion to bd-idcx7 (xattr-at family).","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T22:31:07.215111490Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T22:31:07.215111490Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
