 {"id":"bd-0ebh","title":"syscall: process_vm_readv/writev zero-count NULL iov should succeed without touching errno","description":"Host glibc returns success with errno preserved for process_vm_readv/process_vm_writev when the corresponding iov pointer is NULL and its count is zero. FrankenLibC's raw-syscall wrapper likely already matches, but the ABI suite does not lock that contract down. Add focused regression tests for the zero-count success path.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:03:06.166162809Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T07:05:07.463544883Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T07:05:07.461126174Z","close_reason":"Locked down host-parity zero-count process_vm_readv/process_vm_writev behavior: NULL iov pointers with matching zero counts succeed and preserve errno; verified locally and via rch.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
